oai_dc:dc.dc:title: McCabe Golf Course tee-off, Nashville, Tennessee, 1961 March 10
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: A golf tee-off (unidentified people) at McCabe Park and Golf Course and Recreation Field in Nashville, Tennessee, March 19th, 1961. In 1939, the park board built the McCabe Golf Course which stands at their West Nashville location on Murphy Road in the Sylvan Park neighborhood. The course is named in honor of Charles M. McCabe, a former Chairman of the Park Board. Forms part of Record Group 3, Metro Davidson County Photographer. 1 photograph negative : b & w ; 4 x 5 in.
